Content:
> You can potentially hand over the government contract to the bank for direct collection if:
> - The contract allows it.
> - The government agency agrees.
> - Proper legal steps are followed.
> However, in practice, you need formal approval and careful coordination between all parties. A cessie or tripartite agreement is your best legal path.
> ---
> Legal Frameworks to Reference:
> - KUH Perdata (Indonesian Civil Code) ‚Äì Article 613 (Cessie)
> - Perpres 16/2018 (Procurement) and amendments
> - Permenkeu (Ministry of Finance Regs) on payment procedures
> - LKPP guidelines on contract financing
